node.text:
Data sekuen genom SARS-CoV-2 per 21 Agustus 2020?
?
Basis data GISAID (https://www.gisaid.org) memperlihatkan total genom SARS-CoV-2 yang telah disubmit per 21 Agustus 2020 sebanyak 83.699 sekuen yang berasal dari ratusan negara terjangkit COVID-19, termasuk Indonesia. Dari keseluruhan genom yang sudah disubmit, 91,92% digunakan untuk melakukan pengelompokkan atau klastering SARS-CoV-2 dalam klade S, L, V, G, GH dan GR. ?
?
Dari 18 sekuen genom virus asal pasien Indonesia, mayoritas 72% masuk ke dalam clade L, 22% masuk ke dalam clade GH dan 6% masuk ke dalam clade O di dalam klasifikasi GISAID.?
?
Clade GH yang mengandung mutasi S D614G ditemukan pertama kali dari sampel EPI_ISL_458082 dari Surabaya pada tanggal 9 April 2020 (tanggal koleksi sampel) namun prediksi ini bisa salah karena Indonesia belum memiliki cukup sekuen genom di dalam GISAID.?
?

travelling during a pandemic can be tricky. especially if one is trying to get to australia...

since the aug gov introduced flight caps (to sydney it's 350 per day) planes have been flying with 50 or less passengers. which has resulted in economy class passengers getting bumped from their seats over and over again. 

i was lucky and got my business class ticket for $2'500 AUD. others have had to pay $10'000. just to get home. crazy. expertflier says 23 passengers for my flight into sydney. 15 in business and 8 in economy. and that's in a huge plane.

~Exotic~ is NOT a compliment, it’s racist ? Fetishisation is discrimination. 

Reading this made me feel *SO* seen.

I can’t express to you how 90% of the racism I’ve experienced in my life is due to the fetishisation of my East Asian heritage and proximity to whiteness being an excuse for perpetrators to let this slide.

From people describing me as exotic, oriental, ‘different from other girls’, a ‘beautiful product of colonialism’, remarking on my features and folks even claiming that I peak their ‘yellow fever’, getting constantly compared to some random EurAsian or Asian model. The homogenisation and sexualisation is endless. I even had one person say it’s the first time they’ve ever been with ‘someone like me before’ ? *puke*.

I recently recorded a @badactivistpodcast with @oh_momoko and @celinaxchien where we discuss our experiences with being mixed race East Asian or EurAsian women. Stay tuned for these episodes dropping soon ??

Saturday blessings also come in words and stories. 29 year old Mrs Athukri  Debbarma Aye is the proud owner of Akri Bakes ( @akri_bakes ). Originally from Tripura, her family re-located to Nagaland in 2003. Mrs Akri’s entry to the world of bakers pulled through when she first tasted blueberry cheesecake in Bengaluru. Upon returning home, she struggled to find cheesecake and decided to try making it herself. She would browse through the internet and teach herself how to bake, and eventually learnt a variety of pastries and desserts. As a school teacher, baking was her hobby and a part-time gig. She left her teaching job just this year, attempting a shift in career to Delhi. However, due to the pandemic it did not work out. What therefore started out as a kitchen experiment to an evening hobby, is now popularly known as Akri Bakes. Located in her kitchen in Dimapur, Akri Bakes is popular for its variety of cheesecakes. They also sell buns, bread, patties, roasted chicken, pizza and so on. On asking about the advantage of baking and selling from home , “I can bake at the comfort of my home. No worries about paying extra rent. I mostly use organic products and fresh fruits from our backyard.” Mrs Akri has deep interest in creativity and experimental art, and the freedom baking gives her to do just that motivates her. She concluded, “Despite the pandemic, I would say people’s response have been good. I’m quite happy with the way Akri Bakes is flourishing. Grateful  to God’s favor & the support we have been receiving.”
@akri_bakes delivers home baked goodies at your door step, and it is the only warmth you need to survive the scorching Dimapur heat. Here is to supporting local households, and celebrating our kind bakers.
